         <abstract>
            <p>A necessary and sufficient condition is given for all hyperoblic difference schemes that use up to nine mesh points to be of second-order accuracy. We also construct a new difference scheme for two-dimensional hyperbolic systems of conservation laws. The scheme is of second-order accuracy and requires knowledge of only seven mesh points. A stability condition is obtained and is utilized in numerical computations.</p>
          </abstract>
